## Tested for these things:
- Prisoner's Dilemma game
- Three robot strategies (AlwaysCooperate, AlwaysDefect, TitForTat)
- Round Robin tournament format
- Observer pattern logging system
- Comprehensive test suite


## Design Patterns Used:

### 1. Template Method Pattern
- Robot: Abstract class with getAction() implemented by subclasses
- Game: Abstract class with game-specific rules in subclasses
- Tournament: Abstract class with getBracket() for different formats

### 2. Observer Pattern
- Game acts as Subject
- MoveListener and ScoreListener are Observers
- Separate listener lists for moves and scores

### 3. Strategy Pattern
- Different robot behaviors via getAction() implementation
- Easily extensible for new strategies



### Test Coverage
- RobotTest.java: Tests robot behavior, history tracking, score accumulation
- PrisonersDilemmaTest.java: Tests game logic, scoring matrix, different scenarios
- ListenerTest.java: Tests Observer pattern, file logging, listener management
- RoundRobinTournamentTest.java: Tests tournament structure, matchups, final standings
- IntegrationTest.java: test of complete system

Each class has one clear purpose